.SH NAME
doc_usecases_elektra_web_UC_key_validation_md \- Use Case: Key validation 
 
.SH "Summary"
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBTitle:\fP Key validation
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBScope:\fP Configuration
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBLevel:\fP User Goal
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBActors:\fP User (usually a sysadmin)
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBBrief:\fP User gets feedback about a key's contents\&.
.PP
.SH "Scenarios"
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBExtends:\fP Modifying keys, Adding keys, Drag & Drop keys\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBMain success scenario:\fP If the entered data passes the validation, it is sent to the backend and saved to the key database\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBAlternative scenario:\fP User enters data that fails the field validation, the input field is marked as invalid (e\&.g\&. with a red color and some information text) and the data is NOT sent to the backend\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBAlternative scenario:\fP User enters data that violates a validation rule, an error message is shown and the data is NOT saved to the key database\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBError scenario:\fP Technical problems while persisting to the key database\&. The user is informed about the problem\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBPostcondition:\fP The updated key is persisted to the database\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBNon-functional Constraints:\fP - 
.PP

